snippet.textDisplay:
Hypnotherapy is also suggested for the disorder of Commitment Phobia with Panic Disorder. ex: Fear of love due to severe child abuse. My ex bf was beaten at age 7 by his mother and he stuttered and stayed back in school. He overcame the stuttering, she eventually stopped as he grew. I was with him 18yrs, I saw him panic, run away to come right back. Admitting 'You're right she did something to me' after I figure it out and explained his problem to him. I stayed with him because this wasn't his fault. It says they stay with the abusive parent into old age being a caregiver to the one that hurt him. Trying to fix the damage of love she ruined. He still lives with her 4blocks way from me and will never move out. He left me this year, around our 18yr anniversary saying, "Okay just friends, no more romance for me" and contacts me every 2 mos or so and we get together for a bite to eat. He is a calm guy, never curses, never has anger, a good guy I wanted to grow old with. We are in our late 50's and met at 37/38.
It says CP can be counselled with minor improvements only, the fear stays. It is Hypnotherapy that helps a person with CP to overcome the anxiety and panic of truly loving someone long term in a healthier way.
Oh his dad? He used to hit her with the shoe she was using and battled her back. This was the late 60's He left with her friend and lives in PA. They are all in their 80's now. I haven't been to his mom's 4blks away since 2010 when I figured this out. I told her what I know just as a news flash to her, that what she did was abuse, and when she meets her maker, she will learn she changed his entire destiny. He knows something is wrong, but he avoids the help of hypnotherapy. Which I why I am alone now :/
